He is an ‘international security consultant’ and martial arts expert who was Diana, Princess of Wales’s bodyguard and has worked in troublespots around the world.

Now Lee Sansum is facing a new challenge – as a minder for Alex Salmond in the final, heated days of the referendum campaign as the First Minister tours Scotland.

Pictured standing discreetly, but watchfully, behind the SNP leader, Mr Sansum wears a Yes badge – but insists this is only to help him blend in with the rest of Mr Salmond’s entourage.

